*Section VI. Households enrolled and not covered*

The dashboards cover the following policy management indicators:

a. Households enrolled and not covered - Gender wise
b. Households enrolled and not covered  - Age group wise
c. Households enrolled and not covered -  Facility wise

*Section V. Households with Active Policy*

The dashboards cover the following policy management indicators:

a. Households with active policy - Gender wise
b. Households with active policy  - Age group wise
c. Households with active policy - Based on the period

*Section IV. Individuals enrolled and not covered*

The dashboards cover the following policy management indicators:

a. Individuals enrolled and not covered - Gender wise
b. Individuals enrolled and not covered  - Age group wise
c. Individuals enrolled and not covered -  Facility wise

*Section III. Individuals with Active Policy*

The dashboards cover the following policy management indicators:

a. Individuals with active policy - Gender wise
b. Individuals with active policy  - Age group wise
c. Individuals with active policy - Based on period
d. Individuals with active policy -  Facility wise
e. Individuals with active policy - Education wise
f. Individuals with active policy - Family/Group wise

*Section II: Policy Management Statistics*

The dashboards covers the following policy management indicators:

a. Households/Individuals enrollment vs coverage. 
b. Households and Individuals with new policies.
c. Households and Individuals with renewed policies.
d. Renewable and Re-migration rates (Households and Individuals)

*Section I: Households/Individuals Enrollment Statistics*

The following dashboard gives an overview of the enrollment of Households, Individuals (# and %)

a. Income Status (Poor/Non-Poor)
b. Gender (Male/Female)
c. Enrollments by Provinces/Districts/Facilities
d. Enrollment Rates (individuals, by total population)
